DOLLAR OIL CORPORATION, Ltd., Appellant, v. C. V. IVEY, Appellee. No. 8590. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 2, 1937.

Before DENMAN and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of stipulations of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, without costs, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate' of this court issue forthwith.
